  ('MATH-G4-DH-ELO8', 'MATH-G4-DH', 'Understanding and Applying Concepts of Probability - Predicting and describing the likelihood of events', 268, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('MATH-G4-DH-ELO9', 'MATH-G4-DH', 'Understanding and Applying Concepts of Probability - Calculating Probabilities', 269, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-LS-ELO1', 'LANG-G4-LS', 'The learner will explore, use, and critically apply oral language for pleasure, and personal growth, to foster relationships and to develop an appreciation and celebration of culture and of oral languages.', 270, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-RV-ELO1', 'LANG-G4-RV', 'Students will demonstrate a variety of ways to use background knowledge and interests to select and engage critically with a range of culturally diverse paper based, visual, and digital texts for pleasure and personal growth.', 271, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-RV-ELO2', 'LANG-G4-RV', 'Students will interact with understanding and critical thought to a variety of genres and text forms using vocabulary, comprehension strategies and graphophonic cues.', 272, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-RV-ELO3', 'LANG-G4-RV', 'Students will develop their understanding of how an author’s choice of vocabulary, language, genre, text form, text features and style influence the meaning of text and define the author’s craft.', 273, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-RV-ELO4', 'LANG-G4-RV', 'Learners will generate, gather, and organize thoughts to explore, clarify and reflect on thoughts, feelings, and experiences as they create a written or representative draft, independently and collaboratively, for a range of audiences and purposes.', 274, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-WR-ELO1', 'LANG-G4-WR', 'Students will revise the organization and language use in drafted writing or representation, collaboratively and independently, for a variety of purposes and audiences.', 275, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('LANG-G4-WR-ELO2', 'LANG-G4-WR', 'Students will use their knowledge of spoken language, written language and writing conventions to refine the precision and enhance the meaning and clarity of their written work.', 276, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-E-ELO1', 'SCIENCE-G4-E', ' Use evidence to construct an explanation relating the speed of an object to the energy of that object. ', 277, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-E-ELO2', 'SCIENCE-G4-E', ' Make observations to provide evidence that energy can be transferred from place to place by sound, light, heat, and electric currents.  ', 278, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-E-ELO3', 'SCIENCE-G4-E', ' Ask questions and predict outcomes about the changes in energy that occur when objects collide ', 279, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-E-ELO4', 'SCIENCE-G4-E', ' Apply scientific ideas to design, test, and refine a device that converts energy from one form to another. ', 280, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-E-ELO5', 'SCIENCE-G4-E', 'Obtain and combine information to describe that energy and fuels are derived from natural resources and that their uses affect the environment', 281, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-W-ELO1', 'SCIENCE-G4-W', 'Develop a model of waves to describe patterns in terms of amplitude and wavelength and that waves can cause objects to move ', 282, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-W-ELO2', 'SCIENCE-G4-W', ' Generate and compare multiple solutions that use patterns to transfer information ', 283, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-SF-ELO1', 'SCIENCE-G4-SF', 'Develop a model to describe that light reflecting from objects and entering the eye allows objects to be seen.  ', 284, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-SF-ELO2', 'SCIENCE-G4-SF', 'Construct an argument that plants and animals have internal and external structures that function to support survival, growth, behavior, and reproduction.', 285, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-SF-ELO3', 'SCIENCE-G4-SF', ' Use a model to describe that animals receive different information through their senses, process it in their brain and respond to it differently ', 286, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-PSE-ELO1', 'SCIENCE-G4-PSE', ' Identify evidence from patterns in rock formations and fossils in rock layers to support an explanation for changes in a landscape over time ', 287, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-PSE-ELO2', 'SCIENCE-G4-PSE', 'Make observations and/or measurements to provide evidence of the effects of weathering or the rate of erosion by water, ice, wind, or vegetation', 288, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-PSE-ELO3', 'SCIENCE-G4-PSE', 'Analyze and interpret data from maps to describe patterns of Earth’s features ', 289, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SCIENCE-G4-PSE-ELO4', 'SCIENCE-G4-PSE', 'Generate and compare multiple solutions to reduce the impacts of natural Earth processes on humans ', 290, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SS-G4-HCT-ELO1', 'SS-G4-HCT', 'To recognise that contact with Europeans brought significant changes for Indigenous peoples: Indigenous People in the Caribbean Before Contact', 291, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
  ('SS-G4-HCT-ELO2', 'SS-G4-HCT', 'To recognise that the arrival of Europeans brought significant changes for Indigenous peoples : Indigenous People in the Caribbean and the Impact of the European Arrival', 292, '2026-02-21T17:24:20.767466+00:00'),
